upporting our lives &amp; livelihood!! Instead, we are giving them anger, agony. They are doing their jobs &amp; are saviours!!<\/p>\n<p>Whenever you see anyone of these, please respect and ask them for water or coffee or food. They have been working 24\/7 and mostly without any time for basic nourishment.<\/p>\n<p>Multiculturalism &amp; Respect for all is what I learnt by being an Australian!!<\/p>\n<p>Let\u2019s carry that spirit of care to everywhere around the world!!<\/p>\n<p>If you have any elderly person or any self-isolating family living next to you, just focus on caring, supporting &amp; helping only 2 families &#8211; the ones living next door to your left &amp; right. Get them groceries, food, supplies when you\u2019re getting for yours.<\/p>\n<p>Get flowers for them today and say it &#8211; we\u2019re there &amp; post pics, so others also do. I\u2019m doing it today!!!<\/p>\n<p>These small efforts can create a Human Chain of care, affection &amp; confidence in the community that come what may, we can stand against anything, because, we are together &amp; we\u2019re not mere Indians, Asians, Pakistanis, Chinese, Koreans, Australians, Sikhs, Hindus, Christians, Muslims&#8230;<\/p>\n<p>We are Global Citizens &amp; we care for everyone!!<\/p>\n<p><strong>GD Singh, Chief Executive Officer, Apply4Study<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>#stayathome #coronavirus #COVID19 #australia #weareinthistogether<\/strong><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Be a Global Citizen, Care for everyone &amp; start from your neighborhood!!! &#8211; Something from my heart&#8230; Today in the mid of Global Crisis, Supermarkets staff, Security Guards, Cleaners, Strata people, Bin truck drivers, Aged Care workers, Disability workers, Nurses, Doctors, Police Cops, Public Transport workers, Food\/necessity carriers, drivers, cabbies, Emergency workers, Childcare workers, Airport [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2112,"comment_status":"open","